{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:51:19.071Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b76c70ec88191ad58c75ed1bfc1a4","status":"completed","call_id":"call_NZDzfMazO9G8wADr0lBzM5kO","name":"exec","input":"const r = await tools.exec_command({cmd:\"gh pr view 43 --repo entireio/entire-graph --json title,body,headRefOid,url\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph\",\"yield_time_ms\":10000,\"max_output_tokens\":20000}); text(r.output);\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f74c3-4c30-7912-8b20-fb5d38b32078"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:51:19.697Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","call_id":"call_NZDzfMazO9G8wADr0lBzM5kO","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.6 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"{\"body\":\"<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\\nhttps://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\\n<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\n- Improve deep search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused long-symbol windows, and bounded source reads.\\n- Add `entire graph neighbors` for bounded incoming/outgoing relations and two-hop paths around a located symbol, with agent, text, and JSON formats.\\n- Include file-level callers and constructor invocations in focused call neighborhoods while preserving the underlying relation type in JSON.\\n- Resolve imported/re-exported call targets to their definition locations and prevent arbitrary object methods or non-callable inventory symbols from becoming workspace-global call edges.\\n- Add safe tree-keyed compressed caching for committed `neighbors --head` queries; worktree queries always bypass the cache so dirty edits remain visible.\\n\\nAll changes are general product behavior driven by the query, repository source, imports, symbols, and graph relations. There are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific branches.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nThe realistic Claude Code smoke exposed two separate agent-use gaps:\\n\\n1. Search could locate a symbol but agents had to dump/filter the whole graph or manually reconstruct callers and callees.\\n2. Generic call resolution lost receiver and endpoint semantics in several common cases, creating false edges or omitting file-level callers and constructors.\\n\\nThe focused command gives agents a small structural follow-up after search and makes those relationships complete enough to verify with normal file tools.\\n\\n## Validation\\n\\n- Exact pushed product head: `993813b5a8de8fcf57cb278caa498218698fd9c1`.\\n- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\\n- GitHub Actions passes on Linux, macOS, and Windows (all seven checks).\\n- Real Redux Toolkit verification no longer emits the unrelated `.add()` false edge and now includes the retained top-level `store.ts` caller plus all expected callees.\\n- Real Django verification includes `QueryDict`, `HttpResponseRedirect`, `QueryDict.urlencode`, and `resolve_url` and no longer resolves builtin `list()` to an HTML inventory document.\\n- On the pinned Django tree, a cold full neighborhood took 56.91s and the next query from the same exact cached snapshot took 0.74s.\\n\\n## Development-only agentic smoke\\n\\nThe frozen smoke uses three repositories selected deterministically from the pre-existing retained Tasks corpus: Cobra, Redux Toolkit, and Django. It runs real Claude Code Opus with native file tools for every arm, isolated homes, no session persistence, read-only detached checkouts, no network/history access, and pre/post clean-tree verification.\\n\\nThe full nine-attempt run at product head `e34b154c6f0ac79e3f106dad7d8d8dac0049dcc2` produced:\\n\\n| System | Exact | Macro recall | Micro recall | Tool calls | Wall time | Input incl. cache | Output | Cost |\\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\\n| file tools | 0.833 | 0.917 | 0.753 | 20.0 | 235.1s | 819,991 | 55,844 | $2.6149 |\\n| Entire Graph | 0.778 | 0.944 | 0.856 | 11.7 | 200.6s | 270,290 | 37,645 | $1.6336 |\\n| CBM | 0.833 | 0.877 | 0.670 | 20.7 | 172.0s | 776,642 | 36,524 | $1.9144 |\\n\\nA cost-controlled Entire-Graph-only follow-up at the exact current head `993813b5a8de8fcf57cb278caa498218698fd9c1` produced 0.889 exact, 0.942 macro recall, 0.763 micro recall, 11.3 calls, 186.5s, 371,026 input tokens including cache, 44,554 output tokens, and $1.9932 cost. Cobra and Django were 6/6 exact; Redux was 4/6 because Opus omitted file-level callers and most valid caller×callee combinations from its final summary even though the product output contained the retained caller and all retained callees.\\n\\nThis follow-up is useful development evidence, but it is not a fresh paired control run. It beats the prior controls on exact quality, both recall summaries, tool calls, and input tokens, but it does **not** beat CBM on mean wall time, output tokens, or cost. No universal superiority claim is made.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nThe smoke is development-only and uses an incomplete authored callgraph oracle; it cannot support a confirmatory claim. No V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, publication, or other authorization changed.\\n\",\"headRefOid\":\"0244ef107899b6dd399da1875a4432930b86f38c\",\"title\":\"Improve agent retrieval and focused graph navigation\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/entireio/entire-graph/pull/43\"}\n"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f74c3-4c30-7912-8b20-fb5d38b32078"}}}
