{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:51:44.352Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b76e05a0c8191a3be0a3ccf54e637","status":"completed","call_id":"call_zoVzp7jo0Ohlq76PNGBCph19","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/pr43-body.md\\n+<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\\n+https://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\\n+<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\\n+\\n+## What changed\\n+\\n+- Improve deep search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused long-symbol windows, and bounded source reads.\\n+- Add `entire graph neighbors` for bounded incoming/outgoing relations and two-hop paths around a located symbol, with agent, text, and JSON formats.\\n+- Include file-level callers and constructor invocations while preserving relation types, and cache exact committed-tree snapshots for fast follow-ups.\\n+- Tighten general call resolution: imported/re-exported definition locations, callable-only targets, no arbitrary object-method-to-bare-function collapse, exact JS/TS relative imports, TypeScript abstract declarations, and conservative inherited polymorphic receiver resolution.\\n+\\n+There are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific branches.\\n+\\n+## Why\\n+\\n+Real Claude Code development smoke tests showed that search alone still forced agents to dump/filter whole graphs or manually reconstruct relationships. `neighbors` provides the focused structural follow-up an agent needs after locating a symbol. The later compiler-oracle diagnostic exposed a general TypeScript gap: a Zod neighborhood returned only one of seven real callers and omitted a bodyless abstract target.\\n+\\n+## Validation\\n+\\n+- Exact pushed product head: `0244ef107899b6dd399da1875a4432930b86f38c`.\\n+- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\\n+- The previous pushed head passed all seven Linux/macOS/Windows GitHub checks; checks for this head are running.\\n+- Redux Toolkit: no unrelated `.add()` edge; retained top-level `store.ts` caller and expected callees are present.\\n+- Django: `QueryDict`, `HttpResponseRedirect`, `QueryDict.urlencode`, and `resolve_url` are present; builtin `list()` no longer resolves to an HTML inventory document.\\n+- Zod at the predefined Fidelity ref: repaired output has all 7 compiler-resolved callers (previously 1), the abstract `_parse` target, and only authored `src/helpers/parseUtil.ts:isAsync`; the false `input` construction and generated-mirror duplicate are gone.\\n+- Pinned Django cold neighborhood: 56.91s; same-tree cached follow-up: 0.74s.\\n+\\n+## Development evidence\\n+\\n+The retained Tasks smoke (Cobra, Redux Toolkit, Django) uses non-exhaustive authored assertions. Its metrics are retained-assertion coverage, not all-question exactness. A Graph-only follow-up improved retained coverage and recall while using fewer calls and input tokens, but did not beat CBM on wall time, output, or cost; it is not a universal superiority result.\\n+\\n+A separately frozen compiler-oracle diagnostic used predefined Fidelity repositories (chi, Zod, Click), real Claude Opus, read-only isolated checkouts, no network/history/persistence, and one attempt per repository/treatment:\\n+\\n+| System | Exact | Macro recall | Micro recall | Mean precision | Calls | Wall time | Input incl. cache | Output | Cost |\\n+| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\\n+| file tools | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.7 | 82.6s | 371,759 | 14,581 | $0.9619 |\\n+| Entire Graph | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.3 | 94.3s | 286,523 | 19,989 | $1.1360 |\\n+| CBM | 0.500 | 0.667 | 0.733 | 0.639 | 18.3 | 122.2s | 823,393 | 20,535 | $1.5839 |\\n+\\n+This run is diagnostic-only. It exposed an oracle-scope mismatch: the TypeScript oracle excludes bodyless abstract declarations and the Python oracle excludes class construction, while every successful agent returned those useful relations. Expected answers were not changed after outcomes. A corrected oracle contract must be frozen before another paid run.\\n+\\n+## Scope\\n+\\n+No broad or confirmatory superiority claim is made. No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, publication, or other authorization changed.\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f74c3-4c30-7912-8b20-fb5d38b32078"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:51:44.379Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"exec-1f181175-c82a-42f7-a881-d55a5e004dae","turn_id":"019f74c3-4c30-7912-8b20-fb5d38b32078","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA /private/tmp/pr43-body.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/private/tmp/pr43-body.md":{"type":"add","content":"<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\nhttps://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\n<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\n\n## What changed\n\n- Improve deep search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused long-symbol windows, and bounded source reads.\n- Add `entire graph neighbors` for bounded incoming/outgoing relations and two-hop paths around a located symbol, with agent, text, and JSON formats.\n- Include file-level callers and constructor invocations while preserving relation types, and cache exact committed-tree snapshots for fast follow-ups.\n- Tighten general call resolution: imported/re-exported definition locations, callable-only targets, no arbitrary object-method-to-bare-function collapse, exact JS/TS relative imports, TypeScript abstract declarations, and conservative inherited polymorphic receiver resolution.\n\nThere are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific branches.\n\n## Why\n\nReal Claude Code development smoke tests showed that search alone still forced agents to dump/filter whole graphs or manually reconstruct relationships. `neighbors` provides the focused structural follow-up an agent needs after locating a symbol. The later compiler-oracle diagnostic exposed a general TypeScript gap: a Zod neighborhood returned only one of seven real callers and omitted a bodyless abstract target.\n\n## Validation\n\n- Exact pushed product head: `0244ef107899b6dd399da1875a4432930b86f38c`.\n- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\n- The previous pushed head passed all seven Linux/macOS/Windows GitHub checks; checks for this head are running.\n- Redux Toolkit: no unrelated `.add()` edge; retained top-level `store.ts` caller and expected callees are present.\n- Django: `QueryDict`, `HttpResponseRedirect`, `QueryDict.urlencode`, and `resolve_url` are present; builtin `list()` no longer resolves to an HTML inventory document.\n- Zod at the predefined Fidelity ref: repaired output has all 7 compiler-resolved callers (previously 1), the abstract `_parse` target, and only authored `src/helpers/parseUtil.ts:isAsync`; the false `input` construction and generated-mirror duplicate are gone.\n- Pinned Django cold neighborhood: 56.91s; same-tree cached follow-up: 0.74s.\n\n## Development evidence\n\nThe retained Tasks smoke (Cobra, Redux Toolkit, Django) uses non-exhaustive authored assertions. Its metrics are retained-assertion coverage, not all-question exactness. A Graph-only follow-up improved retained coverage and recall while using fewer calls and input tokens, but did not beat CBM on wall time, output, or cost; it is not a universal superiority result.\n\nA separately frozen compiler-oracle diagnostic used predefined Fidelity repositories (chi, Zod, Click), real Claude Opus, read-only isolated checkouts, no network/history/persistence, and one attempt per repository/treatment:\n\n| System | Exact | Macro recall | Micro recall | Mean precision | Calls | Wall time | Input incl. cache | Output | Cost |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\n| file tools | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.7 | 82.6s | 371,759 | 14,581 | $0.9619 |\n| Entire Graph | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.3 | 94.3s | 286,523 | 19,989 | $1.1360 |\n| CBM | 0.500 | 0.667 | 0.733 | 0.639 | 18.3 | 122.2s | 823,393 | 20,535 | $1.5839 |\n\nThis run is diagnostic-only. It exposed an oracle-scope mismatch: the TypeScript oracle excludes bodyless abstract declarations and the Python oracle excludes class construction, while every successful agent returned those useful relations. Expected answers were not changed after outcomes. A corrected oracle contract must be frozen before another paid run.\n\n## Scope\n\nNo broad or confirmatory superiority claim is made. No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, publication, or other authorization changed.\n"}},"status":"completed"}}
