{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:55:05.677Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Completed the revised three-repository smoke and follow-up repair.\n\nResults:\n\n| System | Exact | Micro recall | Calls | Time | Input incl. cache | Cost |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\n| File tools | 0.667 | 1.000 | 10.7 | 82.6s | 371,759 | $0.9619 |\n| Entire Graph | 0.667 | 1.000 | 10.3 | 94.3s | 286,523 | $1.1360 |\n| CBM | 0.500 | 0.733 | 18.3 | 122.2s | 823,393 | $1.5839 |\n\nEntire Graph tied file tools on measured quality, used fewer calls and 23% fewer input tokens, but did not win latency, output tokens, or cost.\n\nThe smoke also found an oracle mismatch: it penalized abstract TypeScript calls and Python constructors that every successful agent correctly returned. I preserved the original scoring as diagnostic evidence rather than changing expectations after seeing results.\n\nI then fixed the genuine Entire Graph issue:\n\n- Zod callers improved from 1/7 to 7/7.\n- Abstract TypeScript targets are represented.\n- False callable-argument constructions are removed.\n- Exact imports no longer duplicate generated mirror targets.\n- Full local checks and all seven GitHub CI jobs pass.\n\nEntire Graph head: `0244ef1`  \n[PR #43](https://github.com/entireio/entire-graph/pull/43)\n\nBrain-Bench evidence head: `1800a5a`  \n[Diagnostic report](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/oracle-agentic-overlay/diagnostic-run-20260718.md)\n\nNext is to freeze a corrected agent-useful oracle contract on a fresh predefined repository slice. I did not spend money on another run because the authorization covered only this single nine-attempt smoke.\n\n::git-commit{cwd=\"/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph\"}\n::git-push{cwd=\"/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph\" branch=\"codex/improve-search-retrieval\"}\n::git-commit{cwd=\"/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot\"}\n::git-push{cwd=\"/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot\" branch=\"codex/graph-agentic-repair-pilot\"}","phase":"final_answer","memory_citation":null}}
