{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:43:54.823Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"agent_message","id":"amsg_019f7578-20c7-7131-bc10-0a2d61629eb7","author":"/root/evidence_audit","recipient":"/root","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Message Type: FINAL_ANSWER\nTask name: /root\nSender: /root/evidence_audit\nPayload:\nAudit complete; no evidence was changed and no agents were run.\n\nKey finding: the Graph timing defect is worse than one cold start.\n\n- Mandatory `search` had no `--cache-dir`; the standalone runtime had no `ENTIRE_PLUGIN_DATA_DIR`. It therefore built an uncached, query-selected `syntax-only` snapshot.\n- Mandatory `neighbors` used `$TMPDIR/entire-graph-cache` and built a separate repository-wide `full` snapshot.\n- Zod issued another `neighbors` call without `--head`, bypassing the cache and rebuilding again.\n- Attempts also ran three-at-a-time, so local indexing competed across treatments.\n\nTherefore Graph latency cannot be repaired by subtracting a known setup duration. The reported 94.3s versus 82.6s comparison is unusable.\n\nMeasurements that remain valid as raw observations of this exact treatment:\n\n| Metric | File tools | Graph | Difference |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| Frozen exact questions | 8/12 | 8/12 | tie |\n| Frozen expected-item recall | 100% | 100% | tie |\n| Provider input incl. cache | 371,759 | 286,523 | Graph −22.9% |\n| Tool calls | 32 | 31 | Graph −3.1% |\n| Output tokens | 14,581 | 19,989 | Graph +37.1% |\n| Cost | $0.9619 | $1.1360 | Graph +18.1% |\n\nThese are reproducible transcript/billing facts, but not clean causal comparisons because of treatment instructions, the old product defect, and one sample per cell.\n\nThe output gap is entirely Zod:\n\n- Chi: Graph −232 output tokens.\n- Click: Graph +141.\n- Zod: Graph +5,499.\n- Total: Graph +5,408.\n\nOn Zod, Graph used three product calls plus 15 native file calls; file-tools used 14 native calls. The incomplete 1/7 caller result caused effectively the entire file-tools investigation to be repeated. On the complete Chi and Click cases, Graph reduced investigation calls from 6→4 and 9→6 respectively.\n\nFour of the twelve frozen exact failures are oracle-scope penalties, not missed useful relations: abstract `_parse` affected two Zod questions and `_AtomicFile` construction affected two Click questions. Both Graph and file-tools returned them. Had those relations been predeclared, both would be 12/12; that is diagnostic, not a permissible retroactive rescore.\n\nPrompt/treatment biases:\n\n- Graph was forced to call both `search` and `neighbors`; file-tools had no minimum workflow.\n- Graph was explicitly told to “verify or fill gaps” with file tools.\n- Mandatory Graph search added 23,773 result characters despite being unnecessary for these relationship tasks.\n- CBM was told to index during the task and made 21 `index_repository` calls; its latency, calls, tokens, and cost are not preindexed-comparator measurements.\n- Focus symbols were required to have unique names, making targeted grep unusually effective.\n- One attempt per repository/system is insufficient for stable latency or output-token attribution.\n- The compliance audit checked tool presence, not cache hits; it missed Zod’s uncached worktree call.\n\nFair replacement protocol:\n\n1. Freeze the repaired Graph head/binary and an agent-useful oracle that explicitly defines abstract declarations, constructors, and generated mirrors.\n2. Create Graph and CBM indexes outside the agent process and timer; bind them to exact tree, binary/provider version, profile, and ignore/include configuration.\n3. For this callgraph smoke, remove mandatory `search`; prebuild the query-independent full snapshot used by `neighbors`.\n4. Reject any timed Graph attempt that builds a new snapshot, omits `--head`, or misses the expected cache. Disallow CBM index calls during the task.\n5. Use symmetric instructions: assigned retrieval system is primary; file verification is available to every arm only when the agent judges it necessary.\n6. Run attempts serially or with isolated resources, randomized within paired repository blocks, with repetitions.\n7. Report setup/index build and incremental-update cost separately from:\n   - cached retrieval latency;\n   - end-to-end agent latency;\n   - correctness/precision/recall;\n   - model input components and output;\n   - serialized tool-result bytes;\n   - calls and cost.\n8. Use the same three repositories only as a repaired regression smoke. A superiority claim requires a fresh, outcome-blind predefined slice and broader task strata.\n\nOne product implication: current default `search` caches a query-preselected `OnlyFiles` snapshot, and `OnlyFiles` participates in the cache key. A neutral prewarm cannot warm a later arbitrary query. Before semantic-search latency can be benchmarked under the intended boundary, Graph needs a query-independent repository index that timed searches actually reuse, with an auditable cache-hit signal."}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
