{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:00:28.516Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b86fc6e3c8191ae67827a1aa94f02","status":"completed","call_id":"call_lVRkuekXb9RbHPKLsl393KSb","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md\\n+# Preindexed Agentic Measurement Protocol\\n+\\n+The completed `20260718` compiler-oracle smoke remains immutable diagnostic\\n+evidence. Its transcripts, raw records, authorization, recovery record,\\n+scoreboard, report, and overlay documentation are not rescored or rewritten by\\n+this protocol.\\n+\\n+## Historical comparison boundary\\n+\\n+The historical wall-time comparison is invalid. The timed Entire Graph arm was\\n+required to run an uncached selective `search` and a separately cached full\\n+`neighbors` build. One Zod attempt also invoked `neighbors` without `--head`,\\n+which forced another worktree build. The CBM arm was instructed to index during\\n+the task and repeatedly returned a degraded index. These setup costs were inside\\n+the agent timer and competed across concurrent attempts.\\n+\\n+The historical prompt also forced Entire Graph to use `search`, then\\n+`neighbors`, then file-tool verification. The file-tools arm had no comparable\\n+minimum workflow. Consequently, task latency cannot be repaired by subtracting\\n+a single observed indexing duration.\\n+\\n+Raw transcript facts such as returned answers, provider token billing, and tool\\n+calls remain useful diagnostics of that exact treatment. They are not clean\\n+causal estimates for the repaired product or corrected protocol.\\n+\\n+## Replacement protocol\\n+\\n+New runs use `preindexed-agentic-v2` and a new output directory.\\n+\\n+1. Materialize and verify the exact committed repository tree.\\n+2. Build each product index before any paid agent process starts.\\n+3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, profile, and\\n+   isolated cache. Any missing, degraded, corrupt, or cache-miss state aborts\\n+   the whole run before a paid attempt launches.\\n+4. Record setup/index duration separately from task duration.\\n+5. Give each product arm symmetric instructions: use its assigned preindexed\\n+   retrieval system as primary, choose the appropriate retrieval call, and use\\n+   targeted file reads only when useful. Do not force duplicate verification.\\n+6. Require timed Entire Graph calls to use the validated committed-tree cache;\\n+   reject worktree builds, alternate caches, cache misses, and no-cache calls.\\n+7. Reject CBM indexing or project mutation during a timed task.\\n+8. Run attempts without concurrent local indexing. Report cached retrieval and\\n+   end-to-end agent latency separately from setup and incremental-update cost.\\n+\\n+The corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\\n+execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`.\\n+\\n+## Claim boundary\\n+\\n+The same three repositories are a development regression smoke only. They can\\n+verify that diagnosed defects no longer recur, but they cannot support a broad\\n+superiority claim after the outcomes have been observed. A claim requires a\\n+fresh, outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen product and comparator heads,\\n+explicit semantics for abstract declarations, constructors, generated mirrors,\\n+and repeated paired attempts.\\n+\\n+No paid rerun is authorized by this protocol document.\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:00:32.508Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"exec-c063569e-d611-48e5-807a-aba3f9fe7bc4","turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md":{"type":"add","content":"# Preindexed Agentic Measurement Protocol\n\nThe completed `20260718` compiler-oracle smoke remains immutable diagnostic\nevidence. Its transcripts, raw records, authorization, recovery record,\nscoreboard, report, and overlay documentation are not rescored or rewritten by\nthis protocol.\n\n## Historical comparison boundary\n\nThe historical wall-time comparison is invalid. The timed Entire Graph arm was\nrequired to run an uncached selective `search` and a separately cached full\n`neighbors` build. One Zod attempt also invoked `neighbors` without `--head`,\nwhich forced another worktree build. The CBM arm was instructed to index during\nthe task and repeatedly returned a degraded index. These setup costs were inside\nthe agent timer and competed across concurrent attempts.\n\nThe historical prompt also forced Entire Graph to use `search`, then\n`neighbors`, then file-tool verification. The file-tools arm had no comparable\nminimum workflow. Consequently, task latency cannot be repaired by subtracting\na single observed indexing duration.\n\nRaw transcript facts such as returned answers, provider token billing, and tool\ncalls remain useful diagnostics of that exact treatment. They are not clean\ncausal estimates for the repaired product or corrected protocol.\n\n## Replacement protocol\n\nNew runs use `preindexed-agentic-v2` and a new output directory.\n\n1. Materialize and verify the exact committed repository tree.\n2. Build each product index before any paid agent process starts.\n3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, profile, and\n   isolated cache. Any missing, degraded, corrupt, or cache-miss state aborts\n   the whole run before a paid attempt launches.\n4. Record setup/index duration separately from task duration.\n5. Give each product arm symmetric instructions: use its assigned preindexed\n   retrieval system as primary, choose the appropriate retrieval call, and use\n   targeted file reads only when useful. Do not force duplicate verification.\n6. Require timed Entire Graph calls to use the validated committed-tree cache;\n   reject worktree builds, alternate caches, cache misses, and no-cache calls.\n7. Reject CBM indexing or project mutation during a timed task.\n8. Run attempts without concurrent local indexing. Report cached retrieval and\n   end-to-end agent latency separately from setup and incremental-update cost.\n\nThe corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\nexecution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`.\n\n## Claim boundary\n\nThe same three repositories are a development regression smoke only. They can\nverify that diagnosed defects no longer recur, but they cannot support a broad\nsuperiority claim after the outcomes have been observed. A claim requires a\nfresh, outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen product and comparator heads,\nexplicit semantics for abstract declarations, constructors, generated mirrors,\nand repeated paired attempts.\n\nNo paid rerun is authorized by this protocol document.\n"}},"status":"completed"}}
