{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:09:32.172Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b891c20708191bf5496530ebd33ee","status":"completed","call_id":"call_KuCih930NF4KiM0gV5pwRdHN","name":"exec","input":"const r = await tools.exec_command({cmd:\"rg -n \\\"graph search|neighbors|cache-dir|index\\\" README.md docs -g '*.md' | head -200 && git status --short && git diff --stat && git diff --check\",workdir:\"/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph\",yield_time_ms:10000,max_output_tokens:20000}); text(r.output);\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:09:32.409Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","id":"ctco_019f758f-96f9-79a0-8963-44f456497802","call_id":"call_KuCih930NF4KiM0gV5pwRdHN","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.2 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"docs/validation/full-plan-local-proof-20260620.md:984:  fast-profile speed result to full-profile indexing.\nREADME.md:16:entire graph search   --repo . --query \"where is webhook retry handled?\"   # 🔍 ranked code for a task\nREADME.md:57:- **⚡ Scales to millions of relations on one machine.** Real builds: redis at 358K relations in 5.5s, laravel at 1.87M in 17s, micropython at 2.27M in 25.6s. Semantic diffs return in about 0.1s. No indexing service, no cluster.\nREADME.md:58:- **🪶 Lean on memory where it counts.** Memory is released after the build. On repositories it fully indexes, peak stays in tens of MB where the competitor uses hundreds: **80 MB vs 599 MB** (nlohmann/json), **64 vs 285** (koin), **43 vs 225** (Dapper).\nREADME.md:117:| `entire graph search --query \"...\"` | 🔍 Ranked source regions for a natural-language task |\nREADME.md:118:| `entire graph neighbors --symbol NAME` | Direct graph neighbors and bounded two-hop paths for a symbol |\nREADME.md:148:entire graph search --repo . --query \"retry logic for webhook delivery\" --top-k 20 --format agent\nREADME.md:166:- **Cold search** scans files without parsing, then indexes an adaptive pool of 96–256 query-relevant files based on the requested `--top-k`. Shallow searches of up to 20 results retain the 96-file interactive latency bound. Deeper rankings add a corpus-wide sparse pass over eligible files up to 2 MiB, while syntax parsing remains bounded to the adaptive pool; this deliberately spends more time for region recall inside large files. Override the parsing pool with `--max-indexed-files`, or force exhaustive parsing with `--index-all-files`.\nREADME.md:167:- **Profiles.** The default `syntax-only` profile avoids synchronous whole-repository graph construction; `--profile fast` adds local relation expansion when deeper semantic indexing is worth the cost.\nREADME.md:168:- **Caching.** When Entire supplies `ENTIRE_PLUGIN_DATA_DIR`, committed-tree searches reuse a tree-keyed compressed index across invocations. Direct callers can set `--cache-dir`; `--no-cache` disables persistence. Worktree searches never reuse committed indexes, avoiding stale results after edits.\nREADME.md:174:entire graph neighbors --repo . --symbol ExecuteC --file command.go --depth 2 --format agent\nREADME.md:177:`neighbors` reports resolved incoming and outgoing relations with definition\nREADME.md:182:and `--limit` bounds neighbors and paths. The default full profile favors\nREADME.md:187:`--cache-dir`; worktree queries bypass that cache so dirty edits stay visible.\nREADME.md:222:**Cross-service and infrastructure.** Service boundaries (REST routes, gRPC, GraphQL, tRPC, pub/sub channels) are first-class edges, and Dockerfiles, Kubernetes manifests, and Terraform / HCL are indexed as graph nodes with dependency edges.\nREADME.md:244:  entire graph search --repo . --query \"retry logic for webhook delivery\" --format agent\nREADME.md:262:Inside Entire sessions the CLI sets `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` and `ENTIRE_PLUGIN_DATA_DIR` automatically, and committed-tree searches reuse a tree-keyed compressed index across invocations. Outside Entire, pass `--repo`. See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for repo-specific agent instructions.\nREADME.md:317:- **Cached committed-tree search:** reuses a tree-keyed compressed index across invocations when `ENTIRE_PLUGIN_DATA_DIR` is set, so repeated queries on an unchanged tree skip re-parsing.\nREADME.md:371:| `ENTIRE_PLUGIN_DATA_DIR` | Enables the tree-keyed compressed index cache for committed-tree search |\nREADME.md:375:| `--cache-dir` / `--no-cache` | Set or disable the search index cache directory |\nREADME.md:376:| `--max-indexed-files` / `--index-all-files` | Bound or exhaust cold-search parsing |\ndocs/benchmarks.md:59:Pass `-profile full|fast|syntax-only` to measure a given indexing depth (default\ndocs/benchmarks.md:115:  syntax-only skips relation-resolution indexes, oversized generated files emit\ndocs/benchmarks.md:130:  the symbol/index metadata plus a compact relation dedup set (one 64-bit key\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:7:Entire Brain should remain responsible for persistence, indexing, query\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:31:During Phase 1 indexing, `entire-graph` must not:\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:68:or file contents in memory. Peak memory is bounded by the symbol/index metadata\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:119:`--profile full|fast|syntax-only` selects indexing depth (default `full`). The\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:229:relation matrix; emitting millions of C register/header fields adds indexing\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:337:  Blocks are indexed by their referenceable name and references resolved within\ndocs/semantic_provider_requirements.md:417:  types each indexing profile emits (`full`, `fast`, `syntax-only`).\ndocs/baseline-report.md:315:- Header `completeness`: parse/index coverage by language (file + symbol counts)\ndocs/adr/0001-ga-schema-contract.md:8:`entire-graph` emits a semantic index consumed by downstream tools (notably\ndocs/v2-plan.md:78:- Keep deterministic local indexing no-egress.\ndocs/v2-plan.md:107:- `completeness`: aggregate parse/index stats by language and relation type.\ndocs/v2-plan.md:181:  files indexed per second, peak memory if measurable, output bytes, symbol and\ndocs/v2-plan.md:528:- IaC parse failures are localized and do not fail source indexing.\ndocs/v2-plan.md:583:  memory is bounded by symbol/index metadata plus a compact relation dedup set\ndocs/v2-plan.md:586:- Indexing profiles `full|fast|syntax-only` (`--profile`) select indexing\ndocs/v2-plan.md:648:- SQLite stores and indexes.\ndocs/v2-plan.md:696:  schema, graph search, call tracing, impact, snippet retrieval, dead-code, and\n M internal/cli/neighbors.go\n M internal/cli/root.go\n M internal/cli/search.go\n M internal/sem/search.go\n M internal/sem/search_cache.go\n?? internal/cli/index.go\n?? internal/cli/index_test.go\n?? internal/cli/neighbors_efficiency_test.go\n?? internal/sem/search_cache_test.go\n?? internal/sem/search_mirror_dedup.go\n?? internal/sem/search_mirror_dedup_test.go\n internal/cli/neighbors.go    | 139 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------\n internal/cli/root.go         |   5 +-\n internal/cli/search.go       |  25 +++++++-\n internal/sem/search.go       |  18 +++++-\n internal/sem/search_cache.go | 150 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-\n 5 files changed, 310 insertions(+), 27 deletions(-)\n"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
