{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:17:43.182Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b8b07236c8191af1e49657d64345b","status":"completed","call_id":"call_6BUYPLcEza0j6So1RqJAoLeJ","name":"exec","input":"const r = await tools.write_stdin({session_id:81774,chars:\"\",yield_time_ms:30000,max_output_tokens:30000}); text(JSON.stringify(r));\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:17:43.235Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","id":"ctco_019f7597-1443-7091-9814-60b8389fdea6","call_id":"call_6BUYPLcEza0j6So1RqJAoLeJ","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.0 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"{\"chunk_id\":\"bdf46d\",\"wall_time_seconds\":0.000002083,\"exit_code\":0,\"original_token_count\":712,\"output\":\"Review complete — findings written to the plan file. Summary:\\n\\n## Material findings\\n\\n**1. HIGH — the documented preindex warms nothing.** `index` defaults to `syntax-only` (`internal/cli/index.go:92`), README instructs `--profile full`, `search` defaults to `syntax-only` (`internal/cli/search.go:263`), `neighbors` defaults to `full` (`internal/cli/neighbors.go:137`). Profile is in the cache key (`internal/sem/search_cache.go:247`), and both consumers default to `Worktree: true` which bypasses the cache entirely. Follow the README and `index` reports a hit while every later `search` reports `cache-miss`.\\n\\n**2. MEDIUM-HIGH — \\\"serves selective searches without changing their result set\\\" is false.** `filterSearchSnapshot` (`search_cache.go:169-201`) keeps only relations with both endpoints inside the selection; the `OnlyFiles` build path (`provider.go:1232`) instead *resolves* within the selection and synthesizes externals for unresolved targets. Those relations feed `expandGraphCandidates` (`search.go:387`), so ranking depends on whether a full cache entry happens to exist.\\n\\n**3. MEDIUM — filtered snapshot keeps whole-repo `Header.Stats`** (`search_cache.go:173`); warnings and partial failures are filtered, stats are not. Latent, but the header is a frozen 1.x contract and `index.go:83` already publishes it.\\n\\n**4. MEDIUM — agent budget inverts.** `search.go:150-154` clamps the header-adjusted budget to 0, and `fitAgentSearchResults` treats `<= 0` as *unbounded* (`search.go:160`). `--max-context-bytes 20 --format agent` now dumps everything.\\n\\n**5. MEDIUM — mirror dedupe misses the sparse branch.** Applied only to `candidates` (`search.go:408`); sparse candidates join via `selectHybridCandidates` and are hydrated afterwards, so mirrors collapse on shallow searches and reappear on deep ones.\\n\\n**6. MEDIUM — false dedup across sibling monorepo packages.** `searchMirrorPathPair:113` and `:116` short-circuit to `true` with no shared-suffix requirement; combined with the bare-name fallback at `:71`, `packages/a/dist/index.js` and `packages/b/dist/index.js` merge and one result is dropped.\\n\\nPlus four LOW items: `--exclude-tests` over-matching `spec`/`test` dirs and duplicating logic already in `provider.go`; `index` cannot express `--ignore-file`/`--include-file` though they're in the key; JSON/agent divergence on two-hop truncation; orphaned cache temp files.\\n\\n## Checked and clean\\nCache atomicity and Windows rename-while-open semantics; path normalization on every comparison; the `onlyFiles = nil` canonicalization (sound — `filesScanned` shares the `prepareSource` universe); commit-overwrite provenance on tree-keyed hits; the preindex mismatch assertion failing loudly; no-egress; sort determinism of `canonicalSearchPathLess`; dedupe index bookkeeping; Go precedence in the test-suffix chain.\\n\"}"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
