{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:18:10.745Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Opus found six material issues, and I agree with them. The biggest are real product defects, not benchmark caveats: the documented default path can miss the prepared cache; selective cached search can differ from uncached search at cross-file edges; a tiny agent budget becomes unbounded; and deep sparse ranking can bypass mirror deduplication. I’m fixing these now before treating `ada5f27` as a freeze candidate.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
