{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:28:55.610Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","id":"fco_019f75a1-56ba-7752-962d-422da7d7d9db","call_id":"call_oceYImCKqUWvC4DtVLAaydvy","output":"{\"agents\":[{\"agent_name\":\"/root\",\"agent_status\":\"running\"},{\"agent_name\":\"/root/cache_parity_fix\",\"agent_status\":\"running\"},{\"agent_name\":\"/root/harness_audit\",\"agent_status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings, ordered by severity:\\n\\n- [P0] Setup caches are not bound to the product that created them. [run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:519](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:519) validates tree/profile/root but ignores Graph `provider`, `provider_version`, binary SHA, and `graph_source_head`. Existing setup reuse at [line 599](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:599) checks only repository/system/tree plus cache bytes. Meanwhile [lines 979–1002](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:979) accept any existing v2 config and overwrite it. A new `dev` binary can therefore reuse an old `dev` cache while the rewritten config claims a new head/binary. Require exact canonical execution-config equality on resume; bind its SHA, product binary SHA/version, and source head into every setup record.\\n\\n- [P0] Timed protocol violations do not abort. Graph cache misses/cache mutation and CBM timed indexing merely set `treatment_audit.passed = false` at [lines 763–795](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:763); `run()` then continues launching and summarizes the invalid attempts at [lines 1042–1058](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:1042). Persist the transcript/invalid record, then raise before another paid attempt. Invalid records must not contribute ordinary comparison metrics.\\n\\n- [P0] Legacy evidence protection applies only to `run`. `rescore()` at [lines 928–963](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:928) accepts old cold records and emits a scoreboard labeled “preindexed.” Worse, `all` invokes destructive `prepare()` before reaching the guard, and direct `prepare` is unguarded at [lines 1085–1092](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:1085). Put the protocol/output guard before every command-side write and reject legacy records in `rescore`.\\n\\n- [P1] Recovery can launder an old or unrelated transcript into v2. Existing `record.json` is returned without protocol/setup/config validation at [lines 804–807](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:804). A transcript only needs a setup file to be rescored as v2 at [lines 815–863](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:815). Write an `attempt-start.json` before Claude containing execution-config SHA, setup SHA, command/prompt hashes, and product bindings; require it for recovery.\\n\\n- [P1] CBM readiness validation fails open. At [lines 563–565](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:563), `{}`, `{\\\"status\\\":\\\"indexing\\\"}`, or an unexpected status all pass. Require the exact ready state, exact project, nonzero persisted graph, and a second-process retrieval/status proof. During treatment auditing, tools with no result are treated as executed at [lines 621–624](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:621), and CBM response content is never checked for `error`, `degraded`, or missing-project results. Such calls can satisfy `missing_cbm_retrieval`.\\n\\n- [P1] The Graph treatment unnecessarily forces `--index-all-files` at [prompt line 264](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:264) and [audit lines 664–668](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:664). The repaired product already lets selective search reuse the complete preindex while preserving selective-search semantics. Forcing all-files changes normal agent behavior and retrieval latency. Require only HEAD, full profile, exact cache, agent format, and observed cache hit.\\n\\n- [P1] Graph setup accepts a durable but empty or partial index. It does not require expected provider identity, matching provider version, nonzero file/symbol counts, or acceptable warnings at [lines 519–535](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:519). The current test fixture similarly omits all version/content fields at [test line 224](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/test_run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:224).\\n\\n- [P2] Treatment isolation remains porous. Generic Bash is enabled for all arms at [lines 278–284](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:278), and both product binaries are readable in every arm at [line 734](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:734). The audit does not catch Graph `index`, CBM CLI calls, or cross-product use outside recognized retrieval forms. Whitelist/read-enable only the assigned product and reject any comparator executable invocation in other arms.\\n\\n- [P2] Setup evidence is insufficiently committed. `setup.stdout` concatenates multiple JSON responses, and neither stdout/stderr hashes, exact commands, product binding, nor setup environment are recorded at [lines 574–583](/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/tools/run_agentic_tasks_smoke.py:574). The summary also omits `measurement_protocol`.\\n\\nMissing tests should cover exact-config resume rejection, binary/version mismatch, first miss/second hit, empty Graph index, CBM `{}`/`indexing`/retrieval-error responses, abort-after-invalid-treatment, recovery without an attempt-start commitment, `prepare/all/rescore` legacy immutability, workers other than one, and byte-for-byte cache immutability.\\n\\nI made no changes. `git diff --check` and AST parsing passed. The focused pytest suite could not run with the system Python because that interpreter lacks `pytest`.\"}},{\"agent_name\":\"/root/mirror_sparse_fix\",\"agent_status\":\"running\"}]}","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
