{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:30:18.844Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"agent_message","id":"amsg_019f75a2-9bdc-73e3-bac0-a3e1fbf381fe","author":"/root/cache_parity_fix","recipient":"/root","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Message Type: FINAL_ANSWER\nTask name: /root\nSender: /root/cache_parity_fix\nPayload:\nImplemented within the assigned files; no commit or push.\n\nChanges:\n\n- Cache format bumped to v2, preserving internal line/local-symbol metadata.\n- Full preindexes now derive exact selective snapshots by rerunning relation resolution over cached parse output.\n- Cross-boundary imports/types are correctly externalized.\n- Header stats, completeness, warnings, and partial failures are recomputed for selected files.\n- Derived selective snapshots are cached; unsafe derivation falls back to a fresh build.\n- Empty profile options normalize to `full`.\n- `graph index` now defaults to `full`.\n- Added repeatable `--ignore-file` and `--include-file`, passed into the canonical cache key.\n- README documents the default and shared scope flags.\n- Added whole-snapshot cross-file parity, failure-accounting, and CLI cache-key tests.\n\nValidation passed:\n\n- `go test ./internal/sem ./internal/cli -count=1`\n- Focused cache/index tests\n- `git diff --check`\n\nRequired `root.go` help addition:\n\n```text\n[--ignore-file path] [--include-file path]\n```"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
