{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:39:30.680Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b9022a26c819184ffc1c92211a567","status":"completed","call_id":"call_W37GuwBXbam5nrozkoevstkG","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Update File: /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md\\n@@\\n-3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, profile, and\\n-   isolated cache. Any missing, degraded, corrupt, or cache-miss state aborts\\n-   the whole run before a paid attempt launches.\\n+3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, binary hash,\\n+   profile, and isolated cache. Entire Graph must produce a fresh miss followed\\n+   by a hit with nonempty, complete counts. CBM must report the exact indexed\\n+   project and nonzero nodes from a second process. Any missing, degraded,\\n+   corrupt, partial, empty, or unexpected state aborts the whole run before a\\n+   paid attempt launches.\\n@@\\n-6. Require timed Entire Graph calls to use the validated committed-tree cache;\\n-   reject worktree builds, alternate caches, cache misses, and no-cache calls.\\n-7. Reject CBM indexing or project mutation during a timed task.\\n-8. Run attempts without concurrent local indexing. Report cached retrieval and\\n-   end-to-end agent latency separately from setup and incremental-update cost.\\n+6. Require timed Entire Graph search to consume the complete prepared index\\n+   with `--index-all-files`, and require every Graph retrieval to use the exact\\n+   validated committed-tree cache. Reject worktree builds, alternate caches,\\n+   cache misses, no-cache calls, and non-retrieval Graph commands.\\n+7. Reject CBM indexing, CLI use, project mutation, wrong-project retrieval, or\\n+   unhealthy retrieval during a timed task.\\n+8. Commit an `attempt-start.json` before every paid process, binding the prompt,\\n+   command, sandbox, MCP config, setup record, and exact execution config.\\n+   Resume and recovery fail closed when any binding differs.\\n+9. Run both setup and paid attempts sequentially for uncontended latency.\\n+   Persist an invalid transcript and record, then abort before launching another\\n+   paid attempt on any treatment violation.\\n+10. Report cached retrieval and end-to-end agent latency separately from setup\\n+    and incremental-update cost.\\n@@\\n-The corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\\n-execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`.\\n+The corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\\n+execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`, and refuses\\n+to resume when an existing v2 configuration differs byte-for-byte in canonical\\n+content. Prepare, run, recovery, and rescore share the same legacy-evidence\\n+guard.\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:39:37.450Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"exec-6a24acb3-27a7-4b3d-9a6e-5bd776ed293b","turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM /private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot/competitive-eval/preindexed-agentic-v2/README.md":{"type":"update","unified_diff":"@@ -31,5 +31,8 @@\n 2. Build each product index before any paid agent process starts.\n-3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, profile, and\n-   isolated cache. Any missing, degraded, corrupt, or cache-miss state aborts\n-   the whole run before a paid attempt launches.\n+3. Validate the index against the exact tree, product version, binary hash,\n+   profile, and isolated cache. Entire Graph must produce a fresh miss followed\n+   by a hit with nonempty, complete counts. CBM must report the exact indexed\n+   project and nonzero nodes from a second process. Any missing, degraded,\n+   corrupt, partial, empty, or unexpected state aborts the whole run before a\n+   paid attempt launches.\n 4. Record setup/index duration separately from task duration.\n@@ -38,10 +41,22 @@\n    targeted file reads only when useful. Do not force duplicate verification.\n-6. Require timed Entire Graph calls to use the validated committed-tree cache;\n-   reject worktree builds, alternate caches, cache misses, and no-cache calls.\n-7. Reject CBM indexing or project mutation during a timed task.\n-8. Run attempts without concurrent local indexing. Report cached retrieval and\n-   end-to-end agent latency separately from setup and incremental-update cost.\n+6. Require timed Entire Graph search to consume the complete prepared index\n+   with `--index-all-files`, and require every Graph retrieval to use the exact\n+   validated committed-tree cache. Reject worktree builds, alternate caches,\n+   cache misses, no-cache calls, and non-retrieval Graph commands.\n+7. Reject CBM indexing, CLI use, project mutation, wrong-project retrieval, or\n+   unhealthy retrieval during a timed task.\n+8. Commit an `attempt-start.json` before every paid process, binding the prompt,\n+   command, sandbox, MCP config, setup record, and exact execution config.\n+   Resume and recovery fail closed when any binding differs.\n+9. Run both setup and paid attempts sequentially for uncontended latency.\n+   Persist an invalid transcript and record, then abort before launching another\n+   paid attempt on any treatment violation.\n+10. Report cached retrieval and end-to-end agent latency separately from setup\n+    and incremental-update cost.\n \n The corrected runner refuses to write into an evidence directory whose\n-execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`.\n+execution configuration does not declare `preindexed-agentic-v2`, and refuses\n+to resume when an existing v2 configuration differs byte-for-byte in canonical\n+content. Prepare, run, recovery, and rescore share the same legacy-evidence\n+guard.\n \n","move_path":null}},"status":"completed"}}
