{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:44:22.524Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b91467cf8819190b78f081142216a","status":"completed","call_id":"call_keJjTSj0bihwXZAxdA7RfUTf","name":"exec","input":"const calls=[\n tools.exec_command({cmd:\"gh pr view 43 --json body,reviewDecision,reviews,comments\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph\",\"yield_time_ms\":30000,max_output_tokens:20000,sandbox_permissions:\"require_escalated\",justification:\"May I inspect PR #43’s current description and review state so the handoff reflects the final scope?\",\"prefix_rule\":[\"gh\",\"pr\",\"view\"]}),\n tools.exec_command({cmd:\"gh pr view 34 --json body,reviewDecision,reviews,comments\",\"workdir\":\"/private/tmp/brain-bench-graph-agentic-pilot\",\"yield_time_ms\":30000,max_output_tokens:20000,sandbox_permissions:\"require_escalated\",justification:\"May I inspect draft PR #34’s current description and review state so the handoff reflects the corrected protocol?\",\"prefix_rule\":[\"gh\",\"pr\",\"view\"]})\n]; const rs=await Promise.all(calls); text(\"GRAPH\\n\"+rs[0].output+\"\\nBENCH\\n\"+rs[1].output);\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:44:23.165Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call_output","id":"ctco_019f75af-7dfd-78d0-aa6b-4a88b0c47bfc","call_id":"call_keJjTSj0bihwXZAxdA7RfUTf","output":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Script completed\nWall time 0.6 seconds\nOutput:\n"},{"type":"input_text","text":"GRAPH\n{\"body\":\"<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\\nhttps://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\\n<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\n- Improve deep search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused long-symbol windows, and bounded source reads.\\n- Add `entire graph neighbors` for bounded incoming/outgoing relations and two-hop paths around a located symbol, with agent, text, and JSON formats.\\n- Include file-level callers and constructor invocations while preserving relation types, and cache exact committed-tree snapshots for fast follow-ups.\\n- Tighten general call resolution: imported/re-exported definition locations, callable-only targets, no arbitrary object-method-to-bare-function collapse, exact JS/TS relative imports, TypeScript abstract declarations, and conservative inherited polymorphic receiver resolution.\\n\\nThere are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific branches.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nReal Claude Code development smoke tests showed that search alone still forced agents to dump/filter whole graphs or manually reconstruct relationships. `neighbors` provides the focused structural follow-up an agent needs after locating a symbol. The later compiler-oracle diagnostic exposed a general TypeScript gap: a Zod neighborhood returned only one of seven real callers and omitted a bodyless abstract target.\\n\\n## Validation\\n\\n- Exact pushed product head: `0244ef107899b6dd399da1875a4432930b86f38c`.\\n- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\\n- The previous pushed head passed all seven Linux/macOS/Windows GitHub checks; checks for this head are running.\\n- Redux Toolkit: no unrelated `.add()` edge; retained top-level `store.ts` caller and expected callees are present.\\n- Django: `QueryDict`, `HttpResponseRedirect`, `QueryDict.urlencode`, and `resolve_url` are present; builtin `list()` no longer resolves to an HTML inventory document.\\n- Zod at the predefined Fidelity ref: repaired output has all 7 compiler-resolved callers (previously 1), the abstract `_parse` target, and only authored `src/helpers/parseUtil.ts:isAsync`; the false `input` construction and generated-mirror duplicate are gone.\\n- Pinned Django cold neighborhood: 56.91s; same-tree cached follow-up: 0.74s.\\n\\n## Development evidence\\n\\nThe retained Tasks smoke (Cobra, Redux Toolkit, Django) uses non-exhaustive authored assertions. Its metrics are retained-assertion coverage, not all-question exactness. A Graph-only follow-up improved retained coverage and recall while using fewer calls and input tokens, but did not beat CBM on wall time, output, or cost; it is not a universal superiority result.\\n\\nA separately frozen compiler-oracle diagnostic used predefined Fidelity repositories (chi, Zod, Click), real Claude Opus, read-only isolated checkouts, no network/history/persistence, and one attempt per repository/treatment:\\n\\n| System | Exact | Macro recall | Micro recall | Mean precision | Calls | Wall time | Input incl. cache | Output | Cost |\\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\\n| file tools | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.7 | 82.6s | 371,759 | 14,581 | $0.9619 |\\n| Entire Graph | 0.667 | 1.000 | 1.000 | 0.889 | 10.3 | 94.3s | 286,523 | 19,989 | $1.1360 |\\n| CBM | 0.500 | 0.667 | 0.733 | 0.639 | 18.3 | 122.2s | 823,393 | 20,535 | $1.5839 |\\n\\nThis run is diagnostic-only. It exposed an oracle-scope mismatch: the TypeScript oracle excludes bodyless abstract declarations and the Python oracle excludes class construction, while every successful agent returned those useful relations. Expected answers were not changed after outcomes. A corrected oracle contract must be frozen before another paid run.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nNo broad or confirmatory superiority claim is made. No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, publication, or other authorization changed.\\n\",\"comments\":[],\"reviewDecision\":\"\",\"reviews\":[{\"id\":\"PRR_kwDOSqVa0c8AAAABGXDNMg\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"cursor\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"NONE\",\"body\":\"<!-- BUGBOT_REVIEW -->\\nCursor Bugbot has reviewed your changes and found 1 potential issue.\\n\\n\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_FIX_ALL -->\\n<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix All in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>\\n<!-- /BUGBOT_FIX_ALL -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_AUTOFIX_REVIEW_FOOTNOTE_BEGIN -->\\n<sup>❌ Bugbot Autofix is OFF. To automatically fix reported issues with cloud agents, enable autofix in the [Cursor dashboard](https://www.cursor.com/dashboard/bugbot).</sup>\\n<!-- BUGBOT_AUTOFIX_REVIEW_FOOTNOTE_END -->\\n\\nWant fixes drafted automatically? **Bugbot Autofix** can create code changes for findings. A team admin can enable Autofix in the [Cursor dashboard](https://www.cursor.com/dashboard/bugbot/installation/1441364).\\n\\n_Comment `@cursor review` or `bugbot run` to trigger another review on this PR_\\n\\n\\n<sup>Reviewed by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/bugbot) for commit af44ca236d8abc12043b3d3fa6f33e7e2f5ef4ee. Configure [here](https://www.cursor.com/dashboard/bugbot).</sup>\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-07-17T10:28:25Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"reactionGroups\":[],\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"commit\":{\"oid\":\"af44ca236d8abc12043b3d3fa6f33e7e2f5ef4ee\"}}]}\n\nBENCH\n{\"body\":\"## What changed\\n\\n- adds a three-repository, three-treatment Claude Opus repair pilot using native file tools, Entire Graph CLI search, or the full CBM MCP surface\\n- runs balanced treatment rotations in isolated base-only checkouts and captures transcripts, patches, tool use, timing, tokens, costs, test observations, and reference-patch alignment\\n- bootstraps locked dependencies once and clones the exact prepared environment across treatments\\n- records the 2026-07-17 run as development diagnostic evidence, explicitly not a product ranking\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nThe earlier retrieval smoke did not represent how coding agents actually work. This pilot measures the end-to-end investigate/edit/test loop while keeping repository discovery treatment-specific.\\n\\nThe first full run exposed two protocol defects: static shell denies blocked legitimate build/test output filters, and test detection could mistake a runner name in a path for an invocation. Both are fixed; the affected run remains permanently classified as non-rankable.\\n\\n## Safety and scope\\n\\n- stacked on `codex/graph-v7-evidence`; does not modify or retarget PR #29\\n- development-only repositories with opaque bindings\\n- does not inspect V8 identities or change V8 authorization\\n- does not modify Entire Graph or Entire Brain\\n\\n## Validation\\n\\n- `PYTHONPATH=competitive-eval/tools /private/tmp/graph-v7-toolchain-venv/bin/python -m pytest -q competitive-eval/tools/test_run_graph_agentic_repair_pilot.py competitive-eval/tools/test_run_graph_v8_development_smoke.py competitive-eval/tools/test_graph_v8_ranking_worker.py`\\n- 42 tests passed\\n- permission canary confirmed normal shell commands run while explicit denied commands are recorded\\n\",\"comments\":[],\"reviewDecision\":\"\",\"reviews\":[]}\n"}],"internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
