{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:46:03.486Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b91ab72bc819185cd5fdaeaaf963b","status":"completed","call_id":"call_KKaDUKQWpfWFhPfAfVS4zPAx","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/entire-graph-pr43-body.md\\n+<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\\n+https://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\\n+<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\\n+\\n+## What changed\\n+\\n+- Improves agent search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused source windows, and conservative authored/generated mirror deduplication.\\n+- Adds `entire graph neighbors` for bounded callers, callees, constructor edges, and compact exact two-hop path families.\\n+- Completes general Go, TypeScript/JavaScript, and Python call resolution gaps exposed by repository-disjoint development diagnostics.\\n+- Adds `entire graph index`, a durable query-independent HEAD preindex with exact commit/tree/profile/provider provenance, cache-hit telemetry, and repeatable ignore/include scopes.\\n+- Lets committed search and neighbor calls prove they consumed the prepared cache; agent output reports the cache state directly.\\n+- Preserves cache/cold selective-search parity by rerunning relation resolution over cached parse output, with accurate selective completeness stats.\\n+- Keeps positive agent byte budgets bounded and removes generated mirrors from both semantic and deep sparse rankings without merging sibling monorepo packages.\\n+\\n+There are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific product branches.\\n+\\n+## Validation\\n+\\n+- Exact head: `2c54486fc59b4810c2c2ab8443eb32b9bae6811e`.\\n+- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\\n+- All seven Linux/macOS/Windows GitHub checks pass on the exact head.\\n+- Independent Claude Opus review identified cache/default, parity, budget, and mirror-dedup defects; the follow-up commit fixes them with regression coverage.\\n+- The earlier Bugbot focused-region-test issue is already fixed: both tests are independent registered Go tests and execute in the full suite.\\n+\\n+Deterministic replay on the three frozen predefined development repositories, with setup excluded and a fresh cache format:\\n+\\n+| Repository | Cold full setup | Cached search | Cached neighbors | Useful neighborhood |\\n+| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | --- |\\n+| chi | 0.854s | 24ms | 33ms | 1 caller × 6 callees |\\n+| Zod | 5.418s | 62ms | 63ms | 7 callers × 2 callees |\\n+| Click | 3.090s | 57ms | 94ms | 4 callers × 6 callees |\\n+\\n+Every timed retrieval above reported `Index: cache-hit`. Zod includes the real abstract `_parse` target; Click includes the real `_AtomicFile` constructor. Those semantics must be frozen prospectively in any fresh evaluation contract.\\n+\\n+## Evidence boundary\\n+\\n+The previous paid three-repository smoke remains immutable diagnostic evidence, but its wall-time comparison is invalid: Graph and CBM indexing occurred inside the agent timer, Graph was forced through asymmetric duplicate work, CBM was degraded, and attempts competed concurrently. It is not rescored or rewritten here.\\n+\\n+No new paid agentic run is included. A broad superiority claim still requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen comparator/product heads, repeated paired attempts, and the corrected preindexed protocol in Brain-Bench PR #34.\\n+\\n+## Scope\\n+\\n+No Entire Brain changes, V7/V8 catalog/ranking/scoring/publication authorization changes, or benchmark-specific product behavior.\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/brain-bench-pr34-body.md\\n+## What changed\\n+\\n+- Retains the original three-repository, three-treatment Claude Opus repair pilot and its immutable development diagnostics.\\n+- Adds the replacement `preindexed-agentic-v2` protocol for honest agent retrieval comparisons.\\n+- Builds and validates Entire Graph and CBM indexes before any paid process, records setup separately, and requires serial uncontended attempts.\\n+- Requires Entire Graph timed search to consume the complete prepared HEAD cache and every Graph result to prove `Index: cache-hit`.\\n+- Rejects degraded/empty/partial setup, wrong projects/caches, worktree or no-cache Graph calls, timed CBM indexing/CLI use, unhealthy retrieval, and cross-product use.\\n+- Binds every setup to the exact canonical execution config, product binary hash/version, and Graph source head.\\n+- Writes `attempt-start.json` before paid execution, committing prompt, command, MCP config, sandbox, setup, and product bindings; recovery and resume fail closed on any mismatch.\\n+- Preserves an invalid transcript/record and aborts before the next paid attempt when a treatment protocol violation occurs.\\n+- Refuses legacy evidence directories in prepare, run, recovery, and rescore; historical evidence is not relabeled as preindexed.\\n+\\n+## Why\\n+\\n+The frozen 2026-07-18 diagnostic timed product indexing inside the agent task, forced asymmetric Graph work, ran against degraded CBM state, and allowed concurrent local competition. Its raw answers and token records remain useful diagnostics, but its latency comparison is not a causal product comparison.\\n+\\n+The replacement protocol measures the workflow an agent actually receives after project indexing: cached retrieval plus agent reasoning, with setup/index cost reported separately.\\n+\\n+## Validation\\n+\\n+- Exact head: `11d8bc1d93368aa300ca63be0613cba82de284f0`.\\n+- `python3 -m py_compile` passes for runner and tests.\\n+- Focused protocol suite: **30 passed**.\\n+- Coverage includes exact-config resume rejection, source-head/binary setup binding, first miss/second hit, empty/partial Graph rejection, nonready/unhealthy CBM rejection, byte-for-byte cache immutability, serial-worker enforcement, invalid-treatment abort, attempt-start recovery, and legacy rescore immutability.\\n+- The frozen oracle smoke directories and records are unchanged.\\n+\\n+## Safety and scope\\n+\\n+- Draft, stacked on `codex/graph-v7-evidence`; does not modify or retarget PR #29.\\n+- No paid rerun is authorized or included.\\n+- The same three repositories remain development regression diagnostics only, not a broad superiority claim.\\n+- A claim requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen heads, prospectively fixed constructor/abstract/generated-mirror semantics, and repeated paired attempts.\\n+- No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, or publication authorization changes.\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:46:07.437Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"exec-82963831-0d19-4380-bec9-9779520cd6e9","turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA /private/tmp/entire-graph-pr43-body.md\nA /private/tmp/brain-bench-pr34-body.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/private/tmp/brain-bench-pr34-body.md":{"type":"add","content":"## What changed\n\n- Retains the original three-repository, three-treatment Claude Opus repair pilot and its immutable development diagnostics.\n- Adds the replacement `preindexed-agentic-v2` protocol for honest agent retrieval comparisons.\n- Builds and validates Entire Graph and CBM indexes before any paid process, records setup separately, and requires serial uncontended attempts.\n- Requires Entire Graph timed search to consume the complete prepared HEAD cache and every Graph result to prove `Index: cache-hit`.\n- Rejects degraded/empty/partial setup, wrong projects/caches, worktree or no-cache Graph calls, timed CBM indexing/CLI use, unhealthy retrieval, and cross-product use.\n- Binds every setup to the exact canonical execution config, product binary hash/version, and Graph source head.\n- Writes `attempt-start.json` before paid execution, committing prompt, command, MCP config, sandbox, setup, and product bindings; recovery and resume fail closed on any mismatch.\n- Preserves an invalid transcript/record and aborts before the next paid attempt when a treatment protocol violation occurs.\n- Refuses legacy evidence directories in prepare, run, recovery, and rescore; historical evidence is not relabeled as preindexed.\n\n## Why\n\nThe frozen 2026-07-18 diagnostic timed product indexing inside the agent task, forced asymmetric Graph work, ran against degraded CBM state, and allowed concurrent local competition. Its raw answers and token records remain useful diagnostics, but its latency comparison is not a causal product comparison.\n\nThe replacement protocol measures the workflow an agent actually receives after project indexing: cached retrieval plus agent reasoning, with setup/index cost reported separately.\n\n## Validation\n\n- Exact head: `11d8bc1d93368aa300ca63be0613cba82de284f0`.\n- `python3 -m py_compile` passes for runner and tests.\n- Focused protocol suite: **30 passed**.\n- Coverage includes exact-config resume rejection, source-head/binary setup binding, first miss/second hit, empty/partial Graph rejection, nonready/unhealthy CBM rejection, byte-for-byte cache immutability, serial-worker enforcement, invalid-treatment abort, attempt-start recovery, and legacy rescore immutability.\n- The frozen oracle smoke directories and records are unchanged.\n\n## Safety and scope\n\n- Draft, stacked on `codex/graph-v7-evidence`; does not modify or retarget PR #29.\n- No paid rerun is authorized or included.\n- The same three repositories remain development regression diagnostics only, not a broad superiority claim.\n- A claim requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen heads, prospectively fixed constructor/abstract/generated-mirror semantics, and repeated paired attempts.\n- No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, or publication authorization changes.\n"},"/private/tmp/entire-graph-pr43-body.md":{"type":"add","content":"<!-- entire-trail-link-start -->\nhttps://entire.io/gh/entireio/entire-graph/trails/1\n<!-- entire-trail-link-end -->\n\n## What changed\n\n- Improves agent search recall with adaptive syntax preselection, sparse lexical regions, reciprocal-rank fusion, focused source windows, and conservative authored/generated mirror deduplication.\n- Adds `entire graph neighbors` for bounded callers, callees, constructor edges, and compact exact two-hop path families.\n- Completes general Go, TypeScript/JavaScript, and Python call resolution gaps exposed by repository-disjoint development diagnostics.\n- Adds `entire graph index`, a durable query-independent HEAD preindex with exact commit/tree/profile/provider provenance, cache-hit telemetry, and repeatable ignore/include scopes.\n- Lets committed search and neighbor calls prove they consumed the prepared cache; agent output reports the cache state directly.\n- Preserves cache/cold selective-search parity by rerunning relation resolution over cached parse output, with accurate selective completeness stats.\n- Keeps positive agent byte budgets bounded and removes generated mirrors from both semantic and deep sparse rankings without merging sibling monorepo packages.\n\nThere are no repository-, benchmark-, qrel-, rank-, score-, or outcome-specific product branches.\n\n## Validation\n\n- Exact head: `2c54486fc59b4810c2c2ab8443eb32b9bae6811e`.\n- `mise run check` passes: format, vet, build, and `go test -race ./...`.\n- All seven Linux/macOS/Windows GitHub checks pass on the exact head.\n- Independent Claude Opus review identified cache/default, parity, budget, and mirror-dedup defects; the follow-up commit fixes them with regression coverage.\n- The earlier Bugbot focused-region-test issue is already fixed: both tests are independent registered Go tests and execute in the full suite.\n\nDeterministic replay on the three frozen predefined development repositories, with setup excluded and a fresh cache format:\n\n| Repository | Cold full setup | Cached search | Cached neighbors | Useful neighborhood |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | --- |\n| chi | 0.854s | 24ms | 33ms | 1 caller × 6 callees |\n| Zod | 5.418s | 62ms | 63ms | 7 callers × 2 callees |\n| Click | 3.090s | 57ms | 94ms | 4 callers × 6 callees |\n\nEvery timed retrieval above reported `Index: cache-hit`. Zod includes the real abstract `_parse` target; Click includes the real `_AtomicFile` constructor. Those semantics must be frozen prospectively in any fresh evaluation contract.\n\n## Evidence boundary\n\nThe previous paid three-repository smoke remains immutable diagnostic evidence, but its wall-time comparison is invalid: Graph and CBM indexing occurred inside the agent timer, Graph was forced through asymmetric duplicate work, CBM was degraded, and attempts competed concurrently. It is not rescored or rewritten here.\n\nNo new paid agentic run is included. A broad superiority claim still requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen comparator/product heads, repeated paired attempts, and the corrected preindexed protocol in Brain-Bench PR #34.\n\n## Scope\n\nNo Entire Brain changes, V7/V8 catalog/ranking/scoring/publication authorization changes, or benchmark-specific product behavior.\n"}},"status":"completed"}}
