{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T15:22:22.847Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b9a2edb288191ac629e14fc46b0b6","status":"completed","call_id":"call_wywMCJlVPxpikbpj3EN5VGkv","name":"exec","input":"const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /private/tmp/pr34-body.md\\n+## What changed\\n+\\n+- Retains the original three-repository, three-treatment Claude Opus repair pilot and its immutable development diagnostics.\\n+- Adds the replacement `preindexed-agentic-v2` protocol for honest agent retrieval comparisons.\\n+- Builds and validates Entire Graph and CBM indexes before any paid process, records setup separately, and requires serial uncontended attempts.\\n+- Requires Entire Graph timed search to consume the complete prepared HEAD cache and every Graph result to prove `Index: cache-hit`.\\n+- Rejects degraded/empty/partial setup, wrong projects/caches, worktree or no-cache Graph calls, timed CBM indexing/CLI use, unhealthy retrieval, and cross-product use.\\n+- Binds every setup to the exact canonical execution config, product binary hash/version, and Graph source head.\\n+- Writes `attempt-start.json` before paid execution, committing prompt, command, MCP config, sandbox, setup, and product bindings; recovery and resume fail closed on any mismatch.\\n+- Preserves an invalid transcript/record and aborts before the next paid attempt when a treatment protocol violation occurs.\\n+- Refuses legacy evidence directories in prepare, run, recovery, and rescore; historical evidence is not relabeled as preindexed.\\n+- Reconciles the inherited Graph V8 source closure with the already-committed ranking worker and test while preserving ambient probes and false authorization flags.\\n+\\n+## Why\\n+\\n+The frozen 2026-07-18 diagnostic timed product indexing inside the agent task, forced asymmetric Graph work, ran against degraded CBM state, and allowed concurrent local competition. Its raw answers and token records remain useful diagnostics, but its latency comparison is not a causal product comparison.\\n+\\n+The replacement protocol measures the workflow an agent actually receives after project indexing: cached retrieval plus agent reasoning, with setup/index cost reported separately.\\n+\\n+## Validation\\n+\\n+- Exact head: `bcb60c7929241759b2921ead627a8e36b93b0065`.\\n+- `python3 -m py_compile` passes for runner and tests.\\n+- Focused protocol suite: **30 passed**.\\n+- GitHub regression gate: **passed**; 2,376 tests passed, 6 skipped, with frozen V7 evidence, CORE-Bench redaction provenance, and significance-drift checks green.\\n+- Coverage includes exact-config resume rejection, source-head/binary setup binding, first miss/second hit, empty/partial Graph rejection, nonready/unhealthy CBM rejection, byte-for-byte cache immutability, serial-worker enforcement, invalid-treatment abort, attempt-start recovery, and legacy rescore immutability.\\n+- The frozen oracle smoke directories and records are unchanged.\\n+\\n+## Safety and scope\\n+\\n+- Draft, stacked on `codex/graph-v7-evidence`; does not modify or retarget PR #29.\\n+- No paid rerun is authorized or included.\\n+- The same three repositories remain development regression diagnostics only, not a broad superiority claim.\\n+- A claim requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen heads, prospectively fixed constructor/abstract/generated-mirror semantics, and repeated paired attempts.\\n+- No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, or publication authorization changes.\\n*** End Patch\";\nconst result = await tools.apply_patch(patch);\ntext(result);\n","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T15:22:26.342Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"exec-fd5a24f8-3d2f-441c-877e-a9a84971dd8f","turn_id":"019f756f-5147-7222-9084-187ed68d3651","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA /private/tmp/pr34-body.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/private/tmp/pr34-body.md":{"type":"add","content":"## What changed\n\n- Retains the original three-repository, three-treatment Claude Opus repair pilot and its immutable development diagnostics.\n- Adds the replacement `preindexed-agentic-v2` protocol for honest agent retrieval comparisons.\n- Builds and validates Entire Graph and CBM indexes before any paid process, records setup separately, and requires serial uncontended attempts.\n- Requires Entire Graph timed search to consume the complete prepared HEAD cache and every Graph result to prove `Index: cache-hit`.\n- Rejects degraded/empty/partial setup, wrong projects/caches, worktree or no-cache Graph calls, timed CBM indexing/CLI use, unhealthy retrieval, and cross-product use.\n- Binds every setup to the exact canonical execution config, product binary hash/version, and Graph source head.\n- Writes `attempt-start.json` before paid execution, committing prompt, command, MCP config, sandbox, setup, and product bindings; recovery and resume fail closed on any mismatch.\n- Preserves an invalid transcript/record and aborts before the next paid attempt when a treatment protocol violation occurs.\n- Refuses legacy evidence directories in prepare, run, recovery, and rescore; historical evidence is not relabeled as preindexed.\n- Reconciles the inherited Graph V8 source closure with the already-committed ranking worker and test while preserving ambient probes and false authorization flags.\n\n## Why\n\nThe frozen 2026-07-18 diagnostic timed product indexing inside the agent task, forced asymmetric Graph work, ran against degraded CBM state, and allowed concurrent local competition. Its raw answers and token records remain useful diagnostics, but its latency comparison is not a causal product comparison.\n\nThe replacement protocol measures the workflow an agent actually receives after project indexing: cached retrieval plus agent reasoning, with setup/index cost reported separately.\n\n## Validation\n\n- Exact head: `bcb60c7929241759b2921ead627a8e36b93b0065`.\n- `python3 -m py_compile` passes for runner and tests.\n- Focused protocol suite: **30 passed**.\n- GitHub regression gate: **passed**; 2,376 tests passed, 6 skipped, with frozen V7 evidence, CORE-Bench redaction provenance, and significance-drift checks green.\n- Coverage includes exact-config resume rejection, source-head/binary setup binding, first miss/second hit, empty/partial Graph rejection, nonready/unhealthy CBM rejection, byte-for-byte cache immutability, serial-worker enforcement, invalid-treatment abort, attempt-start recovery, and legacy rescore immutability.\n- The frozen oracle smoke directories and records are unchanged.\n\n## Safety and scope\n\n- Draft, stacked on `codex/graph-v7-evidence`; does not modify or retarget PR #29.\n- No paid rerun is authorized or included.\n- The same three repositories remain development regression diagnostics only, not a broad superiority claim.\n- A claim requires a fresh outcome-blind predefined slice, frozen heads, prospectively fixed constructor/abstract/generated-mirror semantics, and repeated paired attempts.\n- No V7/V8 catalog, ranking, scoring, or publication authorization changes.\n"}},"status":"completed"}}
